<paragraph id="79085C025965581058B6C0FBFD825038" blockId="6.[166,1225,203,486]" pageId="6" pageNumber="323">
Species known from almost all of Europe, the Caucasus and some localities on Far East. Its development takes place in many different hubs growing on dead hardwood. The most frequently mentioned species are: 
<taxonomicName id="BEB72781596558105A5BC13BFA325058" box="[566,794,267,293]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Meruliaceae" genus="Bjerkandera" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="323" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="adusta">
<emphasis id="4BC38010596558105A5BC13BFA325058" box="[566,794,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="323">Bjerkandera adusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="BEB72781596558105B4AC13BFD285058" box="[807,1024,267,293]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Fomitopsidaceae" genus="Daedalea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="323" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="quercina">
<emphasis id="4BC38010596558105B4AC13BFD285058" box="[807,1024,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="323">Daedalea quercina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Pers., 
<taxonomicName id="BEB72781596558105C12C13CF81A5038" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Fomes" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="323" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="fomentarius">
<emphasis id="4BC38010596558105C12C13CF81A5038" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="323">Fomes fomentarius</emphasis>
